PREAMBLE: ACKNOWLEDGMENT OF COMMUNITY FUND RECOVERY RIGHTS
Tangem acknowledges that the Software governs access to and interaction with hardware wallets that may hold users' digital assets, cryptocurrencies, and other items of value. Tangem further acknowledges and agrees that:
(a) Dependency Risk. Users of Tangem hardware are dependent upon the continued availability and maintenance of compatible software to access and recover their funds;
(b) Abandonment Scenario. In the event that Tangem AG ceases operations, discontinues maintenance of this repository, becomes insolvent, is acquired, or otherwise fails to provide ongoing support for the Software, users would be unable to recover their funds without the rights granted herein;
(c) Justification for Irrevocable Rights. The irrevocable non-commercial rights granted in this License are specifically intended to ensure that the community retains the perpetual ability to maintain, modify, and distribute the Software as necessary to access and recover funds stored on Tangem hardware, regardless of Tangem's future business status or decisions;
(d) User Protection. Restricting or revoking these rights would constitute an unacceptable risk to users' financial security and property rights, and Tangem expressly disclaims any intent to place users in such a position;
(e) Good Faith Commitment. This acknowledgment represents Tangem's good faith commitment to its user community and shall be interpreted broadly in favor of preserving users' ability to access their own funds.

1. Definitions.
"Software" refers to all contents of this repository.
"Protocol" refers to the proprietary communication protocol, including the sequence of, data structures, and cryptographic methods used to interact with Tangem hardware.
"SDKs" refer to the official Software Development Kits (e.g., for Android, iOS, React Native) provided by Tangem in separate repositories and under their own distinct licenses.
"Non-Commercial Use" means any use that is not primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.
"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the Software.
"Fund Recovery" means any use of the Software intended to access, transfer, manage, or recover digital assets, cryptocurrencies, or other items of value stored on or accessible through Tangem hardware.
